09/09/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the State Investigation and Protection Agency (SIPA) have arrested police officer Stipe Zulj for suspected war crimes committed in 1994 against Serb civilians, local media reported on Tuesday (September 8th). Zulj, 37, holds both BiH and Croatian citizenship. A war crimes prosecutor ordered the arrest after receiving a tip that Zulj has threatened witnesses in the investigation against him. (BHRT, Pincom.info, Dnevni Avaz, Onasa - 08/09/09)
